				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$T\,=\,K/(2\,\times\,r),$$\end{document}T=K∕(2×r),, where r represents the average substitution rate, in this case 1.3×10−8 substitutions per synonymous site per year47.
